The national working committee (NEC) of the Peoples Democratic Party has shifted the date for the conduct of its governorship primaries across the country. The gubernatorial primaries were scheduled to take place on May 21. In the updated timetable, the PDP said the governorship primaries will now take place on May 23. The opposition party also adjusted the dates for state and national assembly primaries as follows: The PDP said the postponed LGA congresses to elect national delegates for the presidential primaries will now take place on May 10. “All aspirants to various positions, critical stakeholders, members of our party across the country as well as relevant agencies of government should please take note,” Debo Ologunagba, PDP spokesperson, said in a statement. The national executive committee (NEC) of the PDP is expected to meet on May 10 to discuss issues affecting the party, including zoning of its presidential ticket.